    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Most ruby developers don't develop using the system ruby - instead they use one of the ruby environment management tools. \n- [RVM](https://rvm.io/)\n- [rbenv](https://github.com/sstephenson/rbenv)\n\nThese make it easier to switch between versions of ruby and in my experience are more up-to-date than the system package.\n\nThe tools also help with the deployment of ruby applications to production - they make it easy to ensure the dev and prod ruby environment are in sync.   As such, I'd rather not have gRPC's installation instructions show how to install a system version of ruby as `sudo apt-get install ruby ruby-dev` does.\n\nThe current [build from source](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/tree/master/src/ruby#build-from-source) instructions suggest installing RVM.  As a way of resolving this issue; would it be ok to move this comment into the [Prerequisites](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/tree/master/src/ruby#prerequisites) section ?\n"
  },
